# Tailwind utility-first (no custom CSS)

- Use **Tailwind utility classes** for all styling in React components.
- Do **not** create or edit custom CSS files for component styling (e.g. `*.css`, `*.scss`, `*.module.css`).
- If styling feels repetitive, extract a **component** or a **small TS helper** (e.g. `cn()`), not a new CSS class.

## Layouts: prefer Flexbox first

- Default to **Flexbox** for layout (`flex`, `flex-col`, `items-*`, `justify-*`, `gap-*`, `flex-wrap`).
- Use CSS Grid only when Flexbox becomes awkward (two-dimensional alignment, masonry-like grids, complex responsive grids).

## Examples

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD: utility-first + flexbox
export function Toolbar() {
  return (
    <div className="flex items-center justify-between gap-3 rounded-lg border border-slate-200 bg-white px-4 py-2">
      <div className="flex items-center gap-2">
        <span className="text-sm font-medium text-slate-900">Orders</span>
        <span className="rounded-full bg-slate-100 px-2 py-0.5 text-xs text-slate-700">12</span>
      </div>
      <button className="inline-flex items-center rounded-md bg-slate-900 px-3 py-1.5 text-sm font-medium text-white hover:bg-slate-800">
        New
      </button>
    </div>
  );
}
```

